post_text:
We wanted to provide you with a quick update in regards to AM drop-off and PM pick-up. Students will no longer be dropped off or picked up at our 7th Street entrance, we will utilize the large parking lot adjacent to Memorial Drive in the AM and PM. After discussions with the Breese Police Department, staff, and community members we feel this will help to alleviate some of the previous issues and will also help keep our students as safe as possible during these times. Please watch the video below for a tutorial of drop-off and pick-up. As stated in the video, please contact me via email (jjohnson@d12bobcats.org) or call the Breese Office (526-7128). Thank you!

**Walkers and bike riders will enter and exit the building via the 7th Street entrance.

post_text:
We are currently seeking the following position:

Transportation Director:

General Responsibilities include developing and administering a transportation system that meets the requirements of the instructional program and extracurricular activities. Ensures compliance with applicable federal, state and local requirements. Responsible for all facets of program administration and operations oversight, including: driver hiring; supervision; scheduling, routing, and dispatching.

Applicants must have a CDL Class B with school bus and passenger endorsement as required by law. Applicants must also be able to pass a background check, drug screen and physical. Please send resume along with references to Mr. Travis Schmale, Superintendent tschmale@d12bobcats.org.

Preschool Screening Information for 2020 School Year:

We do not yet know when we will be able to hold a physical screening for the upcoming school year. We are asking families that are interested in preschool to fill out the Google Form to help us make the screening process as quick as possible when we are allowed to move forward. Our preschool program is grant funded by the state and children that are deemed most at risk are found eligible first. All of the information we are collecting is required by the grant. FILLING OUT THIS FORM DOES NOT GUARANTEE YOUR CHILD A SPOT IN THE PROGRAM. Please contact Jackie Thuenemann with any questions, jthuenemann@d12bobcats.org

Congrats to our two winners of the competition! Blake Heimann (7th grade) and Makenna Ricklefs (7th grade) won gift cards for Dairy King. These gift cards will be brought to the school for pick up at a later date. Thanks to everybody who participated! Remember to stay active, stay healthy, and stay optimistic! We will get through this together, one day at a time!

Fun fact: running will help reduce stress and anxiety. It‚Äôll also help enhance the immune system. Even though there may not be a DK gift card on the line, you will still be rewarded. You will be improving your health mentally and physically and to me, that is the best reward anybody could ever receive!

The best of luck to all of the students the rest of the year!

Stay strong,
Noah Hollenkamp
Head Cross Country Coach

Noah Hollenkamp

post_text:
Just a reminder to our fans and students heading to Rend Lake to watch our Bobcat Boys Basketball team...
Attention Fans:
Section 7. During all Regional and State contests the SIJHSAA prohibits the use of all types of noise-makers, confetti, radios, shakers, poms(unless used by cheerleaders), rally towels, thunder sticks, camera lights, laser lights, and also tripods in the stands. Signs must be no larger than a legal sized sheet of paper. (8 1/2 X 14) Body painting materials shall not be administered at games or containers brought on game sites. Body paint may be worn on arms and the face. Appropriate shirts must be worn to all events. Bands are limited to the National Anthem. They are not to be used to give a home game atmosphere nor to create noise or to rally the fans.
